  "text": "The main energy and trace gas exchanges that occur over coral reefs are shown in Figure 1 , including CO 2 . While coral reefs are known to emit dimethyl sulfide (DMS; and numerous other volatile organic compounds), which may influence cloud microphysical processes, these are not considered further here and readers are directed to, for example, [CITATION_1] , and references therein.",
